       areas. In this case, the zero-one (binary) output option should NOT  be
       used.  Then  the  iinnppuutt map layer can be subtracted from the oouuttppuutt map
       layer using the _r_._m_a_p_c_a_l_c command.  All original non-zero category val-
       ues  will  be  subtracted  out,  leaving  the boundary areas only. This
       resulting zero-one boundary  depiction  can  be  displayed  over  other
       related raster map layers using the overlay option of _d_._r_a_s_t.


       If  the resolution of the current geographic region does not agree with
       the resolution of the input raster map layer, unintended resampling  of
       the  original raster map layer may occur.  The user should be sure that
       the current geographic region is set properly.

